testTask.title: Information about crane used for PV

actions.subDomainEvaluatorInstructions: Record the maximimum capacity of the crane as listed in the Capacity Chart.  Round up to the nearest whole Imperial Ton.

actions.actionsTitle: Please select the Boom and Machinery type for the crawler crane used in delivering this practical exam.

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate must verbally and physically identify different parts of the crane that are necessary to check during a pre-­operation inspection. Note: If the task asks the candidate to identify something that does not exist on the crane (i.e. LMI or hydraulic fluid), select N/A and then bubble in the NA option when completing the answer sheet.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task, you will be responsible for identifying/checking different parts of the crane you will use today.  This task will begin when I read the first item to be identified/checked.  In order to receive credit you must point to the specific piece of the crane you are identifying and must verbally state what item the part represents in the pre-­operation inspection.  I will take notes of the parts you identify but will NOT tell you if you are correct or not.

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate will demonstrate the ability to engage/disengage the drive to walk a crawler crane.  Candidate will be given the track-­travel hand signal to walk the crane.  The candidate will engage the tracks to walk the crane (traveling may NOT be necessary).  The CPE will see that the candidate engages both tracks.  The CPE will then give the stop hand signal.  The CPE will give the hand signal to turn the crane.  The candidate will engage one of the tracks to walk the crane (traveling may NOT be necessary).  The CPE will verify that one of the tracks is engaged.  The CPE will give the hand signal to stop.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task, you will be given the hand signal to travel the crane.  Once you receive the hand signal you will be required to engage the tracks per the hand signals given.

actions.actionsTitle: Proper response to Stop hand signal
Proper response to Stop hand signal 2
Proper response to Travel Both Tracks hand signal

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate must demonstrate how to check the level of the crane.  The candidate will use the onboard level or the available carpenter level (anything 2 ft. or longer) and will place the level on the car body/turn table of the crane.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task you are to check for the levelness of the crane using either the onboard level or carpenter level.  Then give me confirmation that the crane is ready for use.

actions.actionsTitle: Candidate confirms crane is safe to operate

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate will properly respond to the hand signals given by the CPE by operating the crane in response to the hand signals.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task, you will be required to respond to hand signals that I will show you.  When you receive the hand signal, please operate the crane until told otherwise.

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Prior to starting, have the candidate bring the boom back over the front of the crane, fully retracted, ball in a position where the CPE can attach a sling to the end of the ball.  No jib on crane. Candidate will demonstrate that he/she can successfully control the boom and control the load.  For task 5, successful demonstration will be determined by the candidate’s ability to lower a four-­foot sling with a one-­inch shackle onto three targets located at three different places in the range.  The candidate will be scored based on his/her ability to place the shackle onto the target, and to keep the shackle on the target for a period of at least five seconds.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: When instructed, place the shackle inside the target area so that it comes to a rest on the target.  You will start by placing the shackle on Target 1 located the farthest from the crane.   Then place the shackle on the second target located at a distance between Targets 1 and 3.  Finally, place the shackle on the nearest target (Target 3).  When you have placed the shackle on each target, please stop movement of the crane and I will verify the placement of the shackle.  The shackle is to rest on each target for at least five seconds.  Once I give you the signal to proceed, continue to the next target.   Once you have been evaluated on target 3, bring your load to the start of the slalom course.   This is a timed task.  You will have up to 10 minutes to complete this task before you will begin to lose points.  Points will be lost each minute thereafter until you reach 20 minutes, at which time the task will be stopped.

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: In this section, candidate will be required to correctly answer load chart questions. Read each question to the candidate and allow the candidate to answer the question relying on the load chart that comes with the crane.  These questions will vary each time the tests are given, so please ask each question exactly as written. If the crane load chart does not have a stability or structural portion, the candidate can show the range diagram to successfully satisfy question #3.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task, you are to use the load chart provided on the crane to answer the following three questions.

actions.actionsTitle: Using the Capacity Charts and tables supplied by the crane manufacturer, what is the GROSS CAPACITY using the current load radius and current boom length?
Using the Capacity Charts and tables supplied by the crane manufacturer, what is the GROSS CAPACITY at the longest boom length and longest load radius?
Show the CPE the structural portion of the load chart? (Show range diagram if no structural portion is provided)

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate will demonstrate that he/she can successfully control the load.   The candidate will have to navigate a slalom course starting from the Target 3 location. Candidate will be evaluated on his/her ability to navigate around the cones without touching, moving, or bypassing the cones.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: Before beginning the slalom course, I will remove the sling from the hook (or block).  For the slalom course, you are to move your load around each cone according to the diagram I will show you.  Once you have passed the last cone, bring your load down the center between all of the cones.  Then stop your load once you have crossed the start/finish line.  You will be evaluated on your ability to travel through the course with your load without touching, moving or bypassing any of the cones.  You will also be evaluated on your ability to keep the bottom of the hook off of the ground while at the same time NOT raising the bottom of the hook any higher than the top of the cones.  Finally, you will be evaluated on your ability to follow instructions which includes following the outlined direction of the course.  This is a timed task.  You will have up to 15 minutes to complete this task before you will begin to lose points.  Points will be lost each minute thereafter until you reach 30 minutes, at which time the task will be stopped. Before beginning, examine the slalom course to verify that the cones are placed inside of the starting boxes.  You may adjust any cones that are out of alignment.  When you are comfortable with the layout of the slalom course, you may begin.

taskTitles.title: Objective
taskTitles.discription: Candidate will secure the crane.  Activities include: retracting the boom, securing the upper works, boom pawl/dog in, and verbally confirming the crane is secure.

taskTitles.title: Candidate Instructions
taskTitles.discription: In this task, you are to secure the crane.  When you have finished preparing the crane please tell me verbally that the crane is secure.  Once I confirm that the crane is secure, your test is complete.
